1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,279
and five, he provides for us,

2
00:00:02,279 --> 00:00:04,699
he provides for the believers in Corinth,

3
00:00:04,699 --> 00:00:08,159
but of course, as God's word has been preserved for us,

4
00:00:08,159 --> 00:00:11,000
we find that we've learned many valuable lessons

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,539
and valuable aspects about the ministry

6
00:00:14,539 --> 00:00:17,000
that God has given to us.

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,600
We understand, as we looked in chapter number four,

8
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,319
that there will be pressures in ministry,

9
00:00:22,319 --> 00:00:24,639
and there will be pressures that will be internal,

10
00:00:24,639 --> 00:00:26,879
there will be pressures that will be external,

11
00:00:26,879 --> 00:00:28,879
but what I'm rejoicing for is that

12
00:00:28,879 --> 00:00:30,959
though those pressures come,

13
00:00:30,959 --> 00:00:34,000
we understand the provision of God,

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,520
our theme this year, God's grace is sufficient,

15
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:41,520
and we find that God's provision is there,

16
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,720
and it enables us to fulfill the work

17
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,919
that God has given to us.

18
00:00:45,919 --> 00:00:47,520
As we enter into chapter number five,

19
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,840
we find that the ministry that we've been given

20
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:52,819
according to chapter four is defined for us

21
00:00:52,819 --> 00:00:57,560
in chapter five as being the ministry of reconciliation.

22
00:00:57,560 --> 00:01:01,400
And we spoke many weeks talking about that opportunity

23
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:04,279
that we have to be God's ambassadors,

24
00:01:04,279 --> 00:01:06,559
and to find that there are human beings

25
00:01:06,559 --> 00:01:10,360
are at enmity with God because of their sin,

26
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,900
and two parties that are at variance,

27
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:15,279
they need to be reconciled,

28
00:01:15,279 --> 00:01:18,319
and we as ambassadors have been given

29
00:01:18,319 --> 00:01:21,360
the ministry of reconciliation,

30
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:26,360
and we pray you in Christ's stead, be reconciled to God.

31
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:30,199
That's what verse 20 says in 2 Corinthians chapter five,

32
00:01:30,199 --> 00:01:32,680
and I spoke about as we looked at that passage

33
00:01:32,680 --> 00:01:37,000
about the position that we have as ambassadors,

34
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:40,879
and then we had a follow-up message to that subject matter

35
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:43,220
of being a faithful ambassador,

36
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:46,440
and the reality is that if you're a believer this morning,

37
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:48,800
then that means that you're an ambassador,

38
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:52,040
but what kind of an ambassador are we?

39
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:55,680
And what a blessing to understand that God has given to us

40
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:58,360
this ministry of reconciliation.

41
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,839
We believe that the ministry now,

42
00:02:00,839 --> 00:02:02,800
as we come to this sixth chapter,

43
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,819
we find that Paul has explained it.

44
00:02:05,819 --> 00:02:07,839
He explained the ministry.

45
00:02:07,839 --> 00:02:11,000
He wants the people in Corinth and for us this morning

46
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,720
to embrace the ministry,

47
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:17,220
and then to engage in the work that God has given to us.

48
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,919
One of the wonderful things, I mean,

49
00:02:18,919 --> 00:02:21,320
I would say probably the greatest thing about the work,

50
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:23,759
the ministry that God has given to us

51
00:02:23,759 --> 00:02:25,059
is what we're reminded about

52
00:02:25,059 --> 00:02:27,559
as soon as we enter into the sixth chapter.

53
00:02:27,559 --> 00:02:30,399
Notice with me that verse number one tells us this,

54
00:02:30,399 --> 00:02:33,259
we then, and then notice this phrase,

55
00:02:33,259 --> 00:02:37,720
as workers together with him,

56
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:41,520
beseech you also that ye receive not

57
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:44,259
the grace of God in vain.

58
00:02:44,259 --> 00:02:46,199
I've titled the message this morning there

59
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:49,660
from verse number one, workers together with God.

60
00:02:49,660 --> 00:02:51,279
I believe that's the greatest part

61
00:02:51,279 --> 00:02:53,279
or the greatest aspect of the ministry

62
00:02:53,679 --> 00:02:55,559
that we as believers have been given

63
00:02:55,559 --> 00:02:58,919
is that we are workers together with God.

64
00:02:58,919 --> 00:03:00,559
And that's an amazing truth.

65
00:03:00,559 --> 00:03:03,759
In fact, it's actually a truth that the Apostle Paul,

66
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:05,580
under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God,

67
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,839
had shared with this church

68
00:03:07,839 --> 00:03:09,160
in the book of 1 Corinthians.

69
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,440
Hold your place here in chapter six of 2 Corinthians,

70
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,800
but look back, if you will,

71
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:16,559
just very briefly to 1 Corinthians chapter number three.

72
00:03:16,559 --> 00:03:18,679
We find that as the Apostle Paul

73
00:03:18,679 --> 00:03:22,220
is writing to this church now for the second time,

74
00:03:22,259 --> 00:03:24,899
that he reminds them that we are workers together

75
00:03:24,899 --> 00:03:26,500
with him, with God,

76
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:30,779
and we find that he had previously given to them this truth

77
00:03:30,779 --> 00:03:32,000
in 1 Corinthians three.

78
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,139
Notice, if you will, in verse number four,

79
00:03:34,139 --> 00:03:35,419
what was happening in Corinth.

80
00:03:35,419 --> 00:03:38,419
One was saying, I'm of Paul, another I'm of Apollos,

81
00:03:38,419 --> 00:03:40,300
and he says, are you not carnal?

82
00:03:40,300 --> 00:03:42,660
And then he says this, who then is Paul?

83
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:45,619
And who is Apollos?

84
00:03:45,619 --> 00:03:47,960
But ministers, by whom ye believed,

85
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,699
even as the Lord gave to every man,

86
00:03:50,699 --> 00:03:53,460
I have planted, Apollos watered,

87
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:56,100
but God gave the increase.

88
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:59,419
So then neither is he that planteth anything,

89
00:03:59,419 --> 00:04:00,740
neither he that watereth,

90
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:02,639
but God that giveth the increase.

91
00:04:02,639 --> 00:04:04,660
By the way, this is good perspective

92
00:04:04,660 --> 00:04:06,580
for all of us as the people of God.

93
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,699
Paul, many of us would probably say

94
00:04:08,699 --> 00:04:10,619
the greatest Christian that ever lived.

95
00:04:10,619 --> 00:04:12,940
He says, who then is Paul?

96
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,660
Just a minister.

97
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:19,100
He says, as he's writing to Timothy later on,

98
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:21,579
he says that he's the chiefest of sinners,

99
00:04:21,579 --> 00:04:23,019
but he says that we're nothing,

100
00:04:23,019 --> 00:04:25,059
that God is the one that gives the increase.

101
00:04:25,059 --> 00:04:26,619
We're ministering together.

102
00:04:26,619 --> 00:04:27,540
Notice in verse number eight,

103
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:29,260
now he that planteth and he that watereth,

104
00:04:29,260 --> 00:04:30,760
what does he say, are one.

105
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,600
Why?

106
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,540
Because we're workers together,

107
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:34,019
not only with each other, but with God.

108
00:04:34,019 --> 00:04:36,600
It says, and every man shall receive his own reward

109
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,279
according to his own labor,

110
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:41,140
for we are laborers together with God.

111
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:44,799
Ye are God's husbandry, ye are God's building.

112
00:04:44,799 --> 00:04:46,220
And so now as this church,

113
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:48,260
back in 2 Corinthians chapter six,

114
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:50,899
as Paul has spent this lengthy period of time

115
00:04:50,899 --> 00:04:52,980
explaining to them the ministry,

116
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,799
he then shares with them this truth

117
00:04:55,799 --> 00:04:57,920
that we are workers together with God.

118
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:59,579
It wasn't a new truth for them.

119
00:04:59,579 --> 00:05:01,059
If they had read the first letter,

120
00:05:01,059 --> 00:05:04,320
they'd already been aware of this principle of this truth.

121
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:07,119
And I do not believe for many of us here this morning

122
00:05:07,119 --> 00:05:09,299
that this is a new concept or a new truth.

123
00:05:09,299 --> 00:05:11,220
This is something that we're aware of.

124
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,320
But as we dig into the passage of scripture,

125
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:16,459
we find such pertinent information

126
00:05:16,459 --> 00:05:19,260
that needs to be applied in our lives

127
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:21,500
as we seek to fulfill the ministry

128
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,579
that God has given to us.

129
00:05:23,579 --> 00:05:25,100
We're a local church.

130
00:05:25,100 --> 00:05:28,820
As a local church, Christ is the head of our church,

131
00:05:28,820 --> 00:05:31,059
and we find that we have a responsibility

132
00:05:31,059 --> 00:05:34,200
to do the work of Christ that he's left us to do.

133
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,220
We find that as Paul would speak to Timothy,

134
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:37,820
he tells us that we, the church,

135
00:05:37,820 --> 00:05:40,559
are the pillar and ground of the truth.

136
00:05:40,559 --> 00:05:43,739
We have a purpose, and we have a ministry

137
00:05:43,739 --> 00:05:45,320
that has been entrusted to us.

138
00:05:45,320 --> 00:05:47,399
I'm thankful for every missionary

139
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:49,720
that God gives us the opportunity to support

140
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:52,839
around the globe, and we're reminded regularly

141
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:55,260
about missions, and our missions conference

142
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:57,239
is coming up the first week of June,

143
00:05:57,239 --> 00:05:58,239
and we're looking forward to all

144
00:05:58,239 --> 00:06:00,200
that God has in store for us.

145
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:02,000
But I've often said it over the years

146
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,299
that what you will find on that missions map

147
00:06:05,299 --> 00:06:07,359
in our missions directory booklet,

148
00:06:07,359 --> 00:06:10,239
you will not find anywhere on that map

149
00:06:10,239 --> 00:06:13,040
or anywhere in that booklet a missionary

150
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,119
to Fairfax, to Oakton.

151
00:06:15,880 --> 00:06:18,880
And that's why we are the missionaries

152
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:23,880
in Oakton, in Fairfax, in Vienna, this area.

153
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:28,920
God has placed and planted us here for a purpose,

154
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,839
and it's his purpose, and we are engaged in this ministry.

155
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:34,279
If you look at the text of scripture

156
00:06:34,279 --> 00:06:35,959
from verse number one, I want you to notice this

157
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:39,820
if you're taking notes, the partnership of the ministry,

158
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:41,519
the partnership of the ministry.

159
00:06:41,519 --> 00:06:43,200
Now this is something that I've already alluded to

160
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,399
through way of introduction,

161
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,000
and we'll get through these first couple of points

162
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,760
fairly quickly this morning.

163
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:50,040
But we find the partnership of the ministry.

164
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,720
Paul says we then, it's very interesting,

165
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,519
near the end of the fifth chapter,

166
00:06:54,519 --> 00:06:56,559
in fact in chapter four as well,

167
00:06:56,559 --> 00:06:59,559
the apostle Paul speaks to the church in Corinth

168
00:06:59,559 --> 00:07:03,000
with plural emphasis.

169
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,519
He's speaking to them about we and us,

170
00:07:05,519 --> 00:07:08,600
and this partnership of ministry.

171
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,480
The apostle Paul is not just coming in

172
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:13,720
and saying I am, I do.

173
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:17,640
He says we, us, and understanding this partnership,

174
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:21,519
and he says we then, we are partners, co-laborers,

175
00:07:21,519 --> 00:07:24,500
we are on the same team, having the same purpose,

176
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,399
and what a blessing to understand

177
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:28,079
that as the apostle Paul is writing

178
00:07:28,079 --> 00:07:30,660
to this church in Corinth, he says we then,

179
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:34,359
notice what he says, as workers together with him.

180
00:07:34,359 --> 00:07:36,600
We talk about the partnership of the ministry,

181
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:40,440
there's this necessity for cooperation,

182
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:43,320
that we would cooperate one with another,

183
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:44,720
that we understand that we're not

184
00:07:44,720 --> 00:07:46,559
in competition one with another,

185
00:07:46,559 --> 00:07:50,480
no, we are cooperating one with another,

186
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:53,839
and we are seeking not for our own glory,

187
00:07:53,839 --> 00:07:55,480
but for his glory.

188
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:58,839
And we find that when we look at this

189
00:07:58,839 --> 00:08:00,359
partnership of the ministry,

190
00:08:00,359 --> 00:08:03,100
not only are we partners together,

191
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:07,839
but we're partners together with him, with God.

192
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:10,079
Now, I'm encouraged by this greatly.

193
00:08:10,079 --> 00:08:12,179
Many times you've heard, no doubt,

194
00:08:12,179 --> 00:08:15,579
various aspects of the importance of teamwork,

195
00:08:15,579 --> 00:08:17,739
and partnerships, and so on and so forth,

196
00:08:17,739 --> 00:08:20,140
and when I worked in the corporate world

197
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:23,100
for so many years, we had various aspects

198
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:26,540
of dealing with teams, and teamwork,

199
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:29,700
and what could be accomplished by the team

200
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:31,519
is so much greater than what could be accomplished

201
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:34,020
by the individual, and all of these statements

202
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:36,260
that would be made, and I understand

203
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:38,419
the reason for doing that.

204
00:08:38,419 --> 00:08:39,700
But I want you to understand that

205
00:08:39,700 --> 00:08:41,940
when we talk about the work of Christ,

206
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,619
that what's amazing about it is that

207
00:08:44,619 --> 00:08:47,500
it's not just those of us that are gathered here

208
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,859
that are the teammates, or the partners,

209
00:08:49,859 --> 00:08:51,859
that we are co-laborers, that we are

210
00:08:51,859 --> 00:08:54,380
workers together with God.

211
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:56,140
The one who created all things,

212
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,539
the one who has all power, the one who has

213
00:08:58,539 --> 00:09:01,380
all wisdom, the one who has a plan

214
00:09:01,380 --> 00:09:03,539
that is greater than your plan, or my plan,

215
00:09:03,539 --> 00:09:07,020
or our plan collectively, he is the one

216
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:09,900
that we're laboring together with.

217
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:11,039
Isn't that awesome?

218
00:09:11,039 --> 00:09:12,440
I mean, if somebody told you that you could

219
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:15,359
enter into a business endeavor, and I in no way

220
00:09:15,359 --> 00:09:17,520
want you to think that I'm speaking of the church

221
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,520
as being a business, but I'm simply using

222
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:22,080
an analogy this morning, if someone were to tell you

223
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,919
that you have an opportunity to enter

224
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:26,479
into a business endeavor, and that your partner

225
00:09:26,479 --> 00:09:28,559
would have all power, that your partner

226
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:30,320
would have all wisdom, that your partner

227
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,960
would have all resources, you'd be crazy

228
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:35,559
not to enter into the endeavor with that individual.

229
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:40,760
Church is not a business, it's an organism.

230
00:09:41,479 --> 00:09:45,280
It's God's work, and God says that we are

231
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:50,039
laborers together with him, with God.

232
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:53,799
What a blessing that we understand this morning

233
00:09:53,799 --> 00:09:56,159
that the greatest work that's being done

234
00:09:56,159 --> 00:09:59,559
on planet Earth today is the work that God

235
00:09:59,559 --> 00:10:00,400
has accomplished.

236
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:06,600
through his local churches and we have an opportunity as a local church in

237
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:13,300
Oakton, Virginia to be part of what God is doing globally, to be part of what God

238
00:10:13,300 --> 00:10:17,320
is doing in this world. We have an opportunity to support missionaries

239
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:21,400
around the globe. 67 I believe is the number that we're at right now.

240
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:25,960
Different works that we are having the privilege and the opportunity to not

241
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:29,960
only give financially to these missionaries but to pray for them, to

242
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:36,320
understand that they are doing the greatest work on planet Earth. The work

243
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:42,920
of speaking and engaging in the ministry of reconciliation is the greatest work

244
00:10:42,920 --> 00:10:49,000
on planet Earth. Why? As someone said to me recently, the statistics are still

245
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:55,440
true, a hundred percent of the people die. We don't know when we're gonna die but

246
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:59,640
we understand as that appointed unto man wants to die after this the judgment.

247
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:04,320
And when you're engaged in the work of the ministry of reconciliation, you're

248
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:09,000
speaking to individuals about their need for Christ and about the

249
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,600
substitutionary atonement of the Lord Jesus Christ when he took their place

250
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:17,920
and their sin on that cruel cross and he paid that awful price so that they

251
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:23,880
could be redeemed. What an amazing truth. Remember what Jesus said as he gives the

252
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:27,880
Great Commission in Matthew's Gospel as it's recorded for us. He says all power

253
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:32,000
is given unto me in heaven and earth. Go ye therefore. And he tells about preaching

254
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,640
and baptizing and teaching the three aspects of the Great Commission but he

255
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:42,520
ends that passage of scripture by saying and lo I am with you always. Think about

256
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:48,600
that. The Lord Jesus Christ, the power of the Holy Spirit that we go in when we're

257
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:52,840
seeking to fulfill the ministry, we are partners together. He says at the end of

258
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:57,680
